  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Saturday. Bernice came over for what she called a \"media marathon,\" which is basically an excuse to do nothing productive for six straight hours.",
      "zh": "星期六。Bernice 來我家，說要來一場「媒體馬拉松」，基本上就是找個藉口連續六個小時什麼正經事都不做。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We started with cartoons, the kind with silly characters that William still watches but pretends he has outgrown.",
      "zh": "我們從卡通開始，那種角色很蠢的卡通，William 明明還在看，卻假裝自己已經看膩了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One scene made William laugh so hard he fell off the couch, immediately ruining his claim that cartoons are \"for babies now.\"",
      "zh": "有一幕讓 William 笑到直接從沙發上滾下來，馬上把他「卡通是給小寶寶看的」這個說法拆穿了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After cartoons, Bernice pulled out her comic collection, including a rare special edition she is extremely proud of.",
      "zh": "卡通結束後，Bernice 拿出她的漫畫收藏，包括一本她非常自豪的稀有特別版。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This edition only came with a magazine subscription,\" she explained, holding it like it was made of gold, not paper.",
      "zh": "「這個版本只有訂雜誌才會附送，」她解釋道，捧著它的樣子好像那不是紙做的，而是黃金做的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We flipped through an old fashion magazine next, mostly laughing at outdated styles from years before we were even born.",
      "zh": "接下來我們翻了一本舊時尚雜誌，大部分時間都在笑那些我們出生前流行的過時風格。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom walked by and mentioned that one \"outdated\" style in the magazine was actually popular again now, which neither of us wanted to admit was true.",
      "zh": "媽媽經過的時候提到，雜誌裡某個「過時」的風格現在其實又流行起來了，我們兩個都不太想承認這是真的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For lunch break, we watched a short musical clip online, and Bernice insisted on singing along even though she barely knew the melody.",
      "zh": "午休時間，我們在網路上看了一小段音樂劇片段，Bernice 堅持要跟著唱，雖然她根本沒把握旋律。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The song came from a classic album that Sophia apparently used to play on repeat when she was our age.",
      "zh": "那首歌來自一張經典專輯，據說 Sophia 在我們這個年紀的時候會反覆播放。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That melody is older than your parents,\" Sophia said proudly, walking past with a basket of laundry, humming the same tune herself.",
      "zh": "「這旋律比你們爸媽的年紀還大，」Sophia 一邊驕傲地說，一邊抱著一籃衣服經過，自己還哼著同一首曲子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "In the afternoon, we tried reading part of a classic novel assigned for school, but honestly, the dialogue felt slower than anything on our screens.",
      "zh": "下午，我們試著讀一本被指定為經典的小說，但老實說，裡面的對話讀起來比我們螢幕上看的任何東西都還要慢。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice complained that the characters talked for three whole pages before anything actually happened in the scene.",
      "zh": "Bernice 抱怨說，角色講了整整三頁的話，場景裡卻什麼事都還沒發生。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We took a break to write our English essay, comparing an old classic story to a modern pop song, which turned out to be more interesting than expected.",
      "zh": "我們中間休息去寫英文作文，比較一個古典經典故事和一首現代流行歌曲，結果比預期的還有趣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Between shows, we sat through several commercials, one of which used the exact same symbol on every single product it advertised.",
      "zh": "節目之間，我們看了好幾支廣告，其中一支廣告，宣傳的每一項產品上都用了同一個符號。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That symbol is basically their whole brand,\" Bernice said, sounding oddly like the businessman from career day.",
      "zh": "「那個符號基本上就是他們整個品牌的象徵，」Bernice 說，聽起來莫名有點像職業日那位商人的口吻。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We flipped through the TV channels for a while, unable to agree on anything, until we landed on an old black-and-white drama neither of us had heard of.",
      "zh": "我們轉了一陣子電視頻道，什麼都談不攏，直到轉到一部我們都沒聽過的老黑白電視劇。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The drama's dialogue was slow and formal, but the final scene was surprisingly emotional, and Bernice pretended she was not tearing up a little.",
      "zh": "這部劇的對白緩慢又正式，但最後一幕出乎意料地感人，Bernice 假裝自己沒有一點想哭。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time Bernice went home, we had watched cartoons, read comics and a novel, listened to a classic album, and judged an entire fashion magazine.",
      "zh": "等 Bernice 回家的時候，我們已經看了卡通、讀了漫畫和一本小說、聽了一張經典專輯，還評論了整本時尚雜誌。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: a media marathon technically counts as \"resting,\" but somehow my brain feels just as full as it does after a school day.",
      "zh": "今日心得：媒體馬拉松技術上算是「休息」，但不知怎麼地，我的腦子跟上完一整天課一樣塞得滿滿的。"
    }
  ],
